%I A397891 #7 Jul 16 2026 11:38:42
%S A397891 1,0,1,1,4,2,12,16,61,85,310,577,1840,3756,11156,25054,70803,166563,
%T A397891 456460,1113720,2993899
%N A397891 Number of free polysticks (polyedges) with n edges in which no vertex has degree 2.
%C A397891 A polystick (polyedge) is a connected set of unit segments of the square lattice; "free" means counted up to rotations, reflections and translations, as in A019988.
%e A397891 a(1) = 1: the single edge (both vertices have degree 1).
%e A397891 a(2) = 0 because the middle vertex of any 2-edge polystick has degree 2.
%e A397891 a(3) = 1: the T-shape (K_{1,3}: one degree-3 vertex, three leaves); the 3-edge path and the L both contain a degree-2 vertex.
%e A397891 a(4) = 1: the plus (K_{1,4}).
%e A397891 a(5) = 4: all four are trees with degree sequence (3,3,1,1,1,1), i.e. two degree-3 vertices and four leaves; one of them is the H-shape (two parallel 2-edge segments joined by a rung).
%Y A397891 Cf. A397892 (no-degree-two one-sided), A397893 (no-degree-two fixed), A019988 (all free), A151537 (all 1-sided), A096267 (all fixed).
%K A397891 nonn,more,new
%O A397891 1,5
%A A397891 _Dominik Beck_, Jul 14 2026
